		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64211296" name="comment_link_64211296" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23214334&amp;cid=64211296" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64211296)" >Time scales [Re:and we need Nuclear power to...]</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64211296" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64211296); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>3</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~Geoffrey.landis">Geoffrey.landis</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~Geoffrey.landis">( 926948 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64211296"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64211296"><p><div class="quote"><p>Historically, climate isn't stable.</p></div><p>Historically, climate varies on a time scale much longer than the current warming.</p><p>The 100,000-year cycle of glacial advances and retreats during an ice age is indeed blindingly fast on a geological time scale, but it's very slow on a human scale, and far slower than the ~100 year time scale of the current warming.</p><p>We can't attribute the current warming to "historically, climate isn't stable."</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64211296">

