			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64210688"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64210688"><p>The CO2 emissions required to launch 2.5 megatons of hardware into deep space will be enormous. I doubt that much fuel exists on Earth but let's think about the math.</p><p>Let's do a back of the envelope calculation...</p><p>The Falcon Heavy (FH) is probably the most efficient launch vehicle today. It can launch about 44,000 lb into a Mars transfer orbit. That's a fair approximation for a Lagrange point orbit.</p><p>At FH scales, launching 250 megatons into deep space would require 114 million FH launches, expending 772 TRILLI<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64210688">

</div>
